snippet.textDisplay:
You could use some sort of wire mesh to create some sort of grille over the intercooler, the guy's at roadkill did that with their Charger (General Mayhem) and it looked decent. paint it silver to contrast the black or paint it black to go with a stock/ sleeper kind of look. There's a really nice matte black paint that I use when I spray paint. High heat outdoor paint in black gives it a really nice look, almost military-like! also, are you going to weld that intercooler mounting in place? It's not that I don't trust those mounts or your craftmanship, but it would make it a little bit safer. Great video and hope the Yaris build never stops, maybe you could go for a straight pipe or catback exhaust next!

snippet.textDisplay:
It's actually a DENSO ECU, so anyone with a KESS should be able to get an ID and a .bin from AlienTech's database.

There you could edit the injector size and deadtimes, and do some proper tuning (given that you have someone with some real WinOLS experience).

I would much rather do it this way than strapping on a piggyback.

And on that subject? Why not a MegaSquirt or a VEMS?

Both are cheap options and i don't think this has any CAN interface for the instrument and such, it's a Yaris!?
